As you can see in the first, the `message BidRequest` has an array of `message Imp`. Then, in the second link, there are some extensions defined, for example, for `Imp`:

```go
extend com.google.openrtb.BidRequest.Imp {
  // Extension key for AdX Imp.ext.
  optional ImpExt imp = 1009;
}
```

Or for the `BidRequest`:

```go
extend com.google.openrtb.BidRequest {
  // Extension key for the Adx BidRequest.ext
  optional BidRequestExt bid_request = 1018;
}
```

I can add extensions individually for each one:

```go
rtbrequest := &amp;pb.BidRequest{}
bidReqExt := &amp;pb.BidRequestExt{}
proto.SetExtension(rtbrequest, pb.E_BidRequest, bidReqExt);

protoimp := &amp;pb.BidRequest_Imp{}
impExt := &amp;pb.ImpExt{}
proto.SetExtension(protoimp, pb.E_Imp, impExt)
```

But I don&#39;t know how to apply the Imp extensions to the BidRequest, in order to make the `jsonpb.UnmarshalString(message, rtbrequest);` works and avoid the error message: `unknown field &quot;ext&quot; in protobuff.BidRequest_Imp`

